convention in July, saying leaving that option open would be
divisive.
   ``You're saying, `But then there's no role for you, governor.'
That's right. I shouldn't be part of it,'' Cuomo said at the World
Trade Center. ``I should've been in the primaries like everybody
else if I wanted it.''
   Cuomo said he has probably missed his chance to become president.
   ``Since I can't be a candidate this year,'' Cuomo reasoned,
``and the Democrats are going to win for sure, the Democrats will
be in office for eight years. That's the end of Cuomo.''
