<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``We must not forget that many of the worst Nazi hangmen were
Austrians. There were Austrians who were victims and others who
were perpetrators.'' _ Austrian President Kurt Waldheim, in a
speech marking the 50th anniversary of Austria's annexation by Nazi
Germany, apologizing for war crimes committed by his countrymen.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``My decision to resign was reached with great difficulty as I
came to understand how deeply some see the social stature of deaf
persons reflected in the presidency of this university,'' Elisabeth
Ann Zinser, the newly appointed president of Gallaudet University
in Washington, D.C., resigning after students demanded a
hearing-impaired leader for the nation's only liberal arts college
for the deaf.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``We must not go on as if nothing has happened if the initiative
is rejected against our will. We must bring it to a decision in
elections. We may not succeed in this but it is our moral duty to
do so.'' _ Israeli Defense Minister Yitzhak Rabin, urging fellow
Labor Party officials to demand new elections if conservative Prime
Minister Yitzhak Shamir rejects the U.S. peace initiative in the
Middle East.
