<HEAD>Peace Corps Anxious To Negotiate Program For Volunteers In China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Peace Corps officials they're anxious to begin
negotiations with the Chinese to set up the terms of a program
under which agency volunteers for the first time will serve in that
nation.
   Arlen Erdahl, directing of recruiting for the Peace Corps, said
Thursday that applicants started phoning the corps within hours of
the announcement a day earlier that China would begin accepting
Peace Corps volunteers.
   Though the concentration is likely to be on English teachers,
China still must decide what special skills it wants the volunteers
to have, where they will serve and how large the Peace Corps
program would be.
   Erdahl said the agency will have to put volunteers for the
program through a rigorous testing program that rejects four out of
five applicants.
