<HEAD>Efforts To Seek Opposition Merger Called Off</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The opposition Reunification
Democratic Party said today it was abandoning efforts to merge with
the rival Party for Peace and Democracy because Kim Dae-jung
refused to step down as its leader.
   Acting Reunification president Kim Myung-yoon told a news
conference his party would go its own way in preparing for National
Assembly elections expected in late April.
