   Kim Young-sam warned that the opposition would lose to the
governing Democratic Justice Party in the elections if they did not
reunite.
   The parties split last fall when both Kims decided to run in
December's presidential election. That divided the opposition vote
and Roh Tae-woo won without receiving a majority.
   Kim Dae-jung refused Wednesday to resign and instead proposed
that he and Kim Young-sam lead the opposition until the National
Assembly elections, sponsoring joint candidates.
   In a statement, Peace and Democracy spokesman Ahn Dong-seon
charged that Kim Young-sam's obstinacy and meddling was behind his
party's insistence Kim Dae-jung step down.
