<HEAD>8 Die Crossing Flooded River Near Mozambique</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight soldiers guarding the eastern
frontier against rebel incursions were drowned while crossing a
flood-swollen river during a patrol, it was reported today.
   The soldiers of the 61st infantry battalion were drowned in the
Honde River that cuts through the eastern highlands near the border
with Mozambique, according to a Defense Ministry statement
published by the Herald newspaper.
   The victims were a sergeant, three corporals and four privates,
the statement said. It gave no other details.
   Several battalions of Zimbabwe troops are stationed along the
750-mile border following raids by rebels of the Mozambique
National Resistance. The guerrillas have killed more than 40
villagers, abducted scores of others, looted shops and houses and
destroyed government vehicles.
  
