<HEAD>Blast Near American-Affiliated Banks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISTANBUL, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion near two
American-affiliated banks caused light damage but no casualties,
the semi-official Anatolia news agency reported today.
   The blast occurred on the ground floor of a building near the
Saudi American Bank and the Koc American Bank in central Istanbul
around midnight Thursday, Anatolia said.
   The news agency said the explosion damaged two parked cars and
shattered windows of the two banks.
   Police were trying to determine what caused the explosion,
Anatolia said.
   No group claimed responsibility for the blast, it said.
