<DATELINE>LOT, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A regional train derailed near the Brussels
suburb of Lot today, killing one person and injuring 25, the
railroad said.
   The electrical wiring over the train was cut as a result of the
accident, and all service between Brussels and Paris was
temporarily suspended.
