<HEAD>Police Officer Sought in Killing of Wife Found Dead, Apparent
Suicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FLINT, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 23-year police veteran was found dead
Friday in a cemetery of an apparently self-inflicted gunshot wound,
two days after his estranged wife was discovered shot to death.
   Officer Walter Krejcik, 44, was found a few yards from his car
with a .38-caliber pistol near his hand, State Police Lt. Jay
Dornbecker said. He said the death was being treated as a suicide.
   The body of Krejcik's 39-year-old wife, Pamela, was found
Wednesday at her parents' home in Clayton Township. On Thursday,
Krejcik was named in a murder warrant charging him in her death.
   Police said Krejcik's body was found by a worker or a passerby
at Flint Memorial Gardens, within sight of a large stone memorial
to city police officers killed on duty.
   Police said a note and pictures of his children were found near
Krejcik's body.
