<HEAD>Albanian Oil Company Employee Seeks Political Asylum</HEAD>
<DATELINE>IOANNINA, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 25-year-old Albanian oil company
employee seeking political asylum in Greece crawled under an
electric wire fence and gave himself up to authorities, police in
this northern town said Friday.
   The man, identified as Spetim Kenai, from the southern Albanian
town of Fier, crossed the border in daylight Wednesday before
presenting himself at the local police station in the border
village of Pogoniani, a police spokesman said.
   ``He has now been moved to the United Nations refugee center
outside Athens and plans to ask for political asylum,'' said the
spokesman, who requested anonymity in accordance with Greek
practice.
   According to a report in the conservative Athens daily, Free
Press, the man said 17 soldiers and an army officer also recently
fled the self-isolated Balkan state by crossing the border into
Yugoslavia.
