<2ND_LINE>AM-Pie Caper,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Accused of Hiding Gun in Pie</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPENCER, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was being held Friday on charges
she tried to smuggle a gun, hidden in a lemon pie, into the county
jail, authorities said.
   Sherry Spencer, also known as Lea Spencer, 24, of Elkview is
charged with two felony counts of aiding an escape attempt and one
misdemeanor count of carrying a dangerous weapon, Sheriff Robey
Knight said. He would not identify the prisoner to whom Spencer
allegedly was trying to smuggle the weapon.
   Sheriff's Department Sgt. Russell Goodwin said Spencer was
arrested after she showed up at the Roane County Jail on Sunday and
dropped off a lemon pie for a prisoner.
   The pie was in an aluminum dish, and because prisoners are
prohibited from receiving metal objects, a guard transferred the
pie to a paper plate. As he did, Russell said, a .22-caliber pistol
and 13 rounds of ammunition dropped out.
   The gun and ammunition were wrapped in plastic, Russell said.
   Spencer was being held in the Wirt County Jail pending $12,500
bond, Knight said. A preliminary hearing is scheduled Wednesday.
