<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Kennedy,110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rose Kennedy's 14th Great-Grandchild Born</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 14th great-grandchild of matriarch Rose
Kennedy, the mother of President John F. Kennedy, was born Friday
morning at a District of Columbia hospital.
   Officials at the office of Sen. Edward M. Kennedy, D-Mass., said
the senator's niece _ Victoria Lawford Pender, 30, the daughter of
Pat Kennedy Lawford and the late actor Peter Lawford _ gave birth
to an eight-pound, nine-ounce girl at 6:30 a.m. at Georgetown
University Hospital.
   The infant, named Alexandra Lawford Pender, was due on the day
of the Super Tuesday presidential primary elections but arrived a
few days late.
   Ironically her mother, Victoria, was born on Election Day in
1958 when her uncle John Kennedy won re-election to the Senate from
Massachusetts.
   Pender is married to Washington attorney Robert Pender.
   Officials say both mother and child are well.
</TEXT>
