<1ST_LINE>r f PM-TreasuryBills     03-11 0096</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Bills,0099</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rates Rise on One-Year Treasury Bills</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interest rates on 52-week Treasury bills have
risen in the latest auction to the highest level since January.
   The Treasury Department sold $9.03 billion of the bills Thursday
at an average discount rate of 6.3 percent, up from 6.18 percent at
the last auction on Feb. 11.
   The rates were the highest since Jan. 14 when the one-year bills
sold for 6.67 percent. The new discount rate understates the actual
return to investors _ 6.71 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for
$9,363.00.
</TEXT>
